A few months ago, I lost an SSD to a fluke power failure, right before I backed up everything on it to blu-ray. (I use a three-tier system for moving data into "cold storage" and the second/middle tier died.)

All that stuff is probably gone forever, but I've kept up with my backup scheme all the same, and finally today have enough solid archives that I feel reasonably safe again, which is a pleasant relief.

I might actually find the spoons to try a deep data recovery pass on that drive eventually...
